{"parentUuid":"58d6b10d-6008-431f-9add-e78ac16f55ec","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GkXVj2hnECf3jVLHKjmnhw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good context from your CLAUDE.md. You're asking about how to share work between your **personal sandbox** (this WSL environment) and your **corporate identity/environment**.\n\nThe main challenge is: air-gapped or heavily firewalled bank environment, no unrestricted internet, different identity. Here are your realistic options:\n\n---\n\n## Options, ranked by friction\n\n### 1. Git repo with manual export (lowest risk, most auditable)\n- Keep experiments in this sandbox as a Git repo\n- When ready to port, export a clean snapshot: `git archive` or just copy the relevant files\n- Bring in via your corporate laptop's approved channels (USB, internal Git server, email)\n- **Best for**: code, configs, IaC\n\n### 2. Dedicated \"bank-ready\" subfolder convention\n- Within this repo, maintain a `bank-ready/` or `production/` subfolder\n- Apply self-containment rules there from the start (no pypi at runtime, vendored deps, no OAuth, etc.)\n- When porting, you already know it's clean\n- **Best for**: keeping experiments and portable code in the same repo\n\n### 3. Claude Code in both environments (if allowed)\n- If your bank allows Claude Code CLI on a managed laptop, you can share `CLAUDE.md` and memory context\n- The `CLAUDE.md` already captures the migration constraint — that file travels with the code\n- **Best for**: continuity of AI-assisted work across identities\n\n### 4. Container export via `docker save`\n- Build locally with `CL42_` prefix, then `docker save | gzip > myapp.tar.gz`\n- Transfer the tarball; `docker load` on the other side\n- **Best for**: complex runtime environments that are hard to rebuild\n\n---\n\n## My recommendation\n\n**Option 2 + Option 1**: Structure this repo with a `bank-ready/` convention, and use `git archive` to produce clean exports. Your `CLAUDE.md` already documents the constraints — that file should travel with every export.\n\nWant me to set up a `bank-ready/` folder structure or an export script?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":265,"cache_read_input_tokens":16166,"output_tokens":485,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":265,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZLkvgBYxQyTR8b7d1PtS","type":"assistant","uuid":"63bd472f-4a4c-48ae-b4ea-e81bb37c3ef0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T21:56:12.466Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/perni/clexp","sessionId":"59d2df8f-9f57-4ae6-ac44-e716cbc14a65","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"jaunty-stargazing-valley"}
